  <h2>Derby's Real Estate Market: Fast Growth, Different Neighborhoods</h2>
  <p>Derby's changed a lot in the last decade. You've got the established neighborhoods near downtown Derby with 1950s-70s ranch homes where families have been for decades, then you've got the newer subdivisions pushing south and west — Shadow Lakes, Patriot, Westview — where the growth is happening. The houses look completely different, the sellers look different, the problems are different.</p>
  <p>What they have in common is that Derby sellers often need speed. Military families get transfer orders. Growing families buy bigger and need to sell the old place fast. People inherit a house from a parent and don't want it. That's where I come in.</p>

  <h2>Derby Market Context: Price Ranges and Housing Stock</h2>
  <p>Derby homes typically run $150k-$300k depending on age and condition. The downtown and established areas have that 1950s-70s ranch and post-war stock — mostly good bones but aging systems. Roofing, HVAC, electrical updates are common fixes needed. Newer subdivisions are better maintained but you're paying for that.</p>
  <p>McConnell Air Force Base proximity affects the market. You get military families buying when they're posted here, and you get urgent sales when they're reassigned. That creates opportunities for fast transactions. There's also a blue-collar and middle-class vibe to Derby that's different from west Wichita or Andover — people work hard, own homes long-term, but when life changes they need decisive action.</p>

  <h2>Who I Buy From in Derby</h2>
  <p>Military families mostly. PCS orders come down, they have 30 days to close on the new place, and their old Derby home needs to sell now. I've closed deals in 8 days for military sellers because they literally can't wait. Growing families are big too — they bought a 3-bedroom ranch 10 years ago, now they have two kids and need four bedrooms, but the market's slow and they need to move fast. Older homeowners in established neighborhoods, people who've owned the same house 30 years and are ready to downsize.</p>
  <p>I also see divorces in Derby where the house needs to be liquidated quickly and cleanly. Landlords tired of managing problem rental properties. People inheriting properties from parents. Construction workers and Boeing employees facing job changes.</p>

