  <h2>Derby Neighborhoods I Buy In</h2>
  <p><strong>Downtown Derby and Established Areas</strong> — The older, more established neighborhoods near downtown. 1950s-70s ranch homes, mature trees, long-time owner families. Good foundation bones, aging systems common.</p>
  <p><strong>Southeast Derby</strong> — Newer subdivisions with 1990s-2000s construction. Better systems, more move-in ready condition, but also where growing families buy when they upgrade.</p>
  <p><strong>Shadow Lakes</strong> — Newer neighborhood, well-maintained, family-oriented. Relocations and family changes create sales here.</p>
  <p><strong>Patriot and Westview</strong> — The growth edge. Newest construction, 2010s forward. Smaller inventory, but buyer demand is strong so these homes move fast anyway.</p>
  <p><strong>Near McConnell Air Force Base</strong> — Properties within reasonable distance of the base see military buyer activity and military seller relocation pressure.</p>

